2026-04-12: REST with strict pagination and RL
  - Fixed endpoints over GraphQL; avoids field-level authorization complexity and client-driven query unpredictability
  - Offset-limit pagination (default 20, max 100) + keyset pagination for high-offset queries preventing N² complexity
  - RL: 1000 req/min per user, 100 req/min per IP; 50 req/10sec burst allowance
  - Versioning in URL path (v1, v2) for cacheability; 6-month minimum migration period before deprecation
  - Payload wrapper: `{data, meta}` for responses; `{error: {code, message, details}}` for errors
  - X-Request-ID propagated through stack; webhook signatures prevent spoofing
